{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780124062506,"sessionID":"ses_18871130bffewq6n4uHvDBHFVy","part":{"id":"prt_e77a99322001vrLDVctFuaHt3T","messageID":"msg_e77a7f05c001VodRn5j9HLcmCA","sessionID":"ses_18871130bffewq6n4uHvDBHFVy","snapshot":"309c1501f1b9969e74b97e1458c50ae7531226cc","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1780124081454,"sessionID":"ses_18871130bffewq6n4uHvDBHFVy","part":{"id":"prt_e77a9932a0017XeOr3utkmsRtg","messageID":"msg_e77a7f05c001VodRn5j9HLcmCA","sessionID":"ses_18871130bffewq6n4uHvDBHFVy","type":"text","text":"Two clear results: the **time-decay BM25 variant is a success** (finite, nonzero on 19988/19996 rows, row_acc 0.650 — matching Stage2's `score_itemknn_bm25_top3`=0.650130). But the **CW-lite gate still FAILS at 0.4828** even with the zero-fill mismatch eliminated.\n\nSo the task's stated root cause (zero-fill) was real but **not sufficient**. There's a deeper train/inference distribution mismatch. Let me diagnose before patching blindly.\n\nMy hypothesis, directly supported by the task's own hint #3 (\"keep per-user normalization consistent... features must be on the same scale as inference\"): the logit uses **raw absolute features**. Training negatives are community-popularity sampled (very popular), but the eval split uses sqrt-pop negatives (less popular). So the logit learns \"high absolute popularity → negative\" and that confound **inverts** at inference (~0.48 = sign-flipped). Within-user normalizing the features (identically for train pairs and candidates) removes the absolute-popularity confound and keeps only the within-slate ranking signal the top-half metric actually uses.\n\nLet me verify this empirically with a caching harness so I can A/B raw-vs-normalized cheaply (the heavy feature frames computed once).","time":{"start":1780124062507,"end":1780124081422}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780124081543,"sessionID":"ses_18871130bffewq6n4uHvDBHFVy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"tooluse_NiDLhuXFrJf4qiGf2V3Ale","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"import sys, time\nfrom pathlib import Path\nsys.path.insert(0, \"scripts\")\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\n\nfrom paper_guided_next_steps import (\n    FeatureConfig, build_feature_frame, sample_weighted_training_pairs,\n    feature_columns, load_train_interactions, load_pairs_csv,\n)\nfrom recsys_played_utils import normalize_within_user, evaluate_tophalf\n\nsplit = Path(\"artifacts/validation/val_random_sqrtpop_seed42\")\nraw = Path(\"data/raw/public/data/train.json\")\ncache = Path(\"artifacts/_smoke_scratch\")\nfcfg = FeatureConfig(seed=42, cw_max_users=2000, cw_max_pos_per_user=20)\n\ntr = load_train_interactions(split / \"train_interactions.csv\")\ncand = load_pairs_csv(split / \"candidates.csv\")\n\ncand_cache = cache / \"cand_scored.parquet\"\ntrain_cache = cache / \"train_scored.parquet\"\n\nif cand_cache.exists() and train_cache.exists():\n    cand_scored = pd.read_parquet(cand_cache)\n    train_scored = pd.read_parquet(train_cache)\n    print(\"[cache] loaded frames\")\nelse:\n    t0 = time.time()\n    cand_scored, _ = build_feature_frame(tr, cand, raw, fcfg)\n    print(f\"[build] candidate frame {time.time()-t0:.1f}s\")\n    t0 = time.time()\n    train_pairs = sample_weighted_training_pairs(tr, seed=fcfg.seed, max_users=fcfg.cw_max_users, max_pos_per_user=fcfg.cw_max_pos_per_user)\n    train_scored, _ = build_feature_frame(tr, train_pairs, raw, fcfg)\n    print(f\"[build] train-pair frame {time.time()-t0:.1f}s\")\n    cand_scored.to_parquet(cand_cache)\n    train_scored.to_parquet(train_cache)\n    print(\"[cache] saved frames\")\n\nfcols = feature_columns(cand_scored)\nprint(f\"n feature cols: {len(fcols)}\")\n\nfrom sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\nfrom sklearn.pipeline import make_pipeline\nfrom sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n\ndef fit_eval(use_norm):\n    if use_norm:\n        tnorm = normalize_within_user(train_scored, fcols)\n        cnorm = normalize_within_user(cand_scored, fcols)\n        cols = [f\"z_{c}\" for c in fcols]\n        Xtr = tnorm[cols].replace([np.inf,-np.inf],0.0).fillna(0.0).to_numpy(np.float32)\n        Xc  = cnorm[cols].replace([np.inf,-np.inf],0.0).fillna(0.0).to_numpy(np.float32)\n    else:\n        Xtr = train_scored[fcols].replace([np.inf,-np.inf],0.0).fillna(0.0).to_numpy(np.float32)\n        Xc  = cand_scored[fcols].replace([np.inf,-np.inf],0.0).fillna(0.0).to_numpy(np.float32)\n    y = train_scored[\"Label\"].astype(int).to_numpy()\n    w = train_scored[\"sample_weight\"].astype(float).to_numpy()\n    clf = make_pipeline(StandardScaler(), LogisticRegression(max_iter=250, C=0.7, solver=\"lbfgs\", random_state=42))\n    clf.fit(Xtr, y, logisticregression__sample_weight=w)\n    pred = cand_scored.copy()\n    pred[\"cw\"] = clf.decision_function(Xc).astype(np.float32)\n    s,_ = evaluate_tophalf(pred, \"cw\", label_col=\"Label\", user_col=\"userID\", id_col=\"ID\", tie_cols=[(\"pop_count\",True),(\"gameID\",False)])\n    return s[\"row_accuracy\"], s[\"per_user_mean_accuracy\"]\n\nraw_acc = fit_eval(False)\nnorm_acc = fit_eval(True)\nprint(f\"RAW   features: row_acc={raw_acc[0]:.6f} user_acc={raw_acc[1]:.6f}\")\nprint(f\"NORM  features: row_acc={norm_acc[0]:.6f} user_acc={norm_acc[1]:.6f}\")\n","filePath":"/opt/data/kaggle/kmu-rec-sys-26-steam/artifacts/_smoke_scratch/ab_norm.py"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/opt/data/kaggle/kmu-rec-sys-26-steam/artifacts/_smoke_scratch/ab_norm.py","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"artifacts/_smoke_scratch/ab_norm.py","time":{"start":1780124081412,"end":1780124081541}},"id":"prt_e77a9dcf1001yoi50L7K1vgqvj","sessionID":"ses_18871130bffewq6n4uHvDBHFVy","messageID":"msg_e77a7f05c001VodRn5j9HLcmCA"}}
