{"type":"text","timestamp":1780124348280,"sessionID":"ses_18871130bffewq6n4uHvDBHFVy","part":{"id":"prt_e77adcd30001Kpy19FNEILpPcZ","messageID":"msg_e77ad7f87001Rh2XMzMyXs524e","sessionID":"ses_18871130bffewq6n4uHvDBHFVy","type":"text","text":"**Diagnosis confirmed.** The zero-fill was real but not the whole story. With raw absolute features, training negatives are community-pop sampled (very popular games) while the eval split uses sqrt-pop negatives — so the logit learns \"high popularity → not played\" and that confound **sign-flips at inference** (0.4828, worse than random). Within-user normalizing the features identically for train pairs and candidates (exactly task hint #3) removes the absolute-scale confound: **0.5651 ≥ 0.55 → PASS**.\n\nThe cache is warm now. Let me confirm z-score is the best within-user option vs. percentile-rank before locking in the fix.","time":{"start":1780124339505,"end":1780124348275}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780124348376,"sessionID":"ses_18871130bffewq6n4uHvDBHFVy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"tooluse_BDwmIVnPX3Uo8ktxABUC19","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"import sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\nsys.path.insert(0, \"scripts\")\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom paper_guided_next_steps import FeatureConfig, feature_columns\nfrom recsys_played_utils import normalize_within_user, evaluate_tophalf\nfrom sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\nfrom sklearn.pipeline import make_pipeline\nfrom sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n\ncache = Path(\"artifacts/_smoke_scratch\")\ncand_scored = pd.read_parquet(cache / \"cand_scored.parquet\")\ntrain_scored = pd.read_parquet(cache / \"train_scored.parquet\")\nfcols = feature_columns(cand_scored)\n\ntnorm = normalize_within_user(train_scored, fcols)\ncnorm = normalize_within_user(cand_scored, fcols)\ny = train_scored[\"Label\"].astype(int).to_numpy()\nw = train_scored[\"sample_weight\"].astype(float).to_numpy()\n\ndef run(prefix, label):\n    cols = [f\"{prefix}{c}\" for c in fcols]\n    cols = [c for c in cols if c in tnorm.columns and c in cnorm.columns]\n    Xtr = tnorm[cols].replace([np.inf,-np.inf],0.0).fillna(0.0).to_numpy(np.float32)\n    Xc  = cnorm[cols].replace([np.inf,-np.inf],0.0).fillna(0.0).to_numpy(np.float32)\n    clf = make_pipeline(StandardScaler(), LogisticRegression(max_iter=250, C=0.7, solver=\"lbfgs\", random_state=42))\n    clf.fit(Xtr, y, logisticregression__sample_weight=w)\n    pred = cand_scored.copy()\n    pred[\"cw\"] = clf.decision_function(Xc).astype(np.float32)\n    s,_ = evaluate_tophalf(pred, \"cw\", label_col=\"Label\", user_col=\"userID\", id_col=\"ID\", tie_cols=[(\"pop_count\",True),(\"gameID\",False)])\n    print(f\"{label}: row_acc={s['row_accuracy']:.6f} user_acc={s['per_user_mean_accuracy']:.6f} (ncols={len(cols)})\")\n\nrun(\"z_\", \"within-user z-score\")\nrun(\"pct_rank_\", \"within-user pct_rank\")\n","filePath":"/opt/data/kaggle/kmu-rec-sys-26-steam/artifacts/_smoke_scratch/ab_norm2.py"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/opt/data/kaggle/kmu-rec-sys-26-steam/artifacts/_smoke_scratch/ab_norm2.py","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"artifacts/_smoke_scratch/ab_norm2.py","time":{"start":1780124348230,"end":1780124348373}},"id":"prt_e77adef30001secR3ZoXR6jTwM","sessionID":"ses_18871130bffewq6n4uHvDBHFVy","messageID":"msg_e77ad7f87001Rh2XMzMyXs524e"}}
