{"type":"text","timestamp":1780124372546,"sessionID":"ses_18871130bffewq6n4uHvDBHFVy","part":{"id":"prt_e77ae3f86001SEj14KYpAmkW8w","messageID":"msg_e77ae2209001F2tZhBn0nODmrO","sessionID":"ses_18871130bffewq6n4uHvDBHFVy","type":"text","text":"z-score wins decisively (0.565 vs 0.505 for pct_rank). The fix is: within-user z-score normalize the logit features identically for train pairs and candidates. This satisfies task requirements #1 (same pipeline), #3 (consistent per-user normalization), and #4 (gate). Let me update `todos` and implement.","time":{"start":1780124368774,"end":1780124372541}}}
