{"type":"text","timestamp":1780124763336,"sessionID":"ses_18871130bffewq6n4uHvDBHFVy","part":{"id":"prt_e77b4189a001YEZIpBw37q7zY9","messageID":"msg_e77b40887001CYxaHFnnjG2EAL","sessionID":"ses_18871130bffewq6n4uHvDBHFVy","type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nFixed the CW-lite scorer and added the time-decay BM25 ItemKNN variant in `scripts/paper_guided_next_steps.py` (single-file change; safety posture untouched).\n\n**CW-lite fix (the bug went deeper than the spec's stated root cause):**\n- Eliminated the zero-fill mismatch by routing CW training pairs through the **same** `build_feature_frame` pipeline as candidates (new `FeatureConfig` + `build_feature_frame` are the single source of truth), with a hard `RuntimeError` guard replacing the silent zero-fill (req #1, #2).\n- That alone was **not** enough — the smoke still scored **0.4828** (worse than random). I A/B-tested and found the real driver: with raw absolute features, the logit keys on absolute popularity, and since train negatives (community-pop) and the eval split's negatives (sqrt-pop) differ in scale, the decision boundary **sign-flips at inference**. Within-user z-scoring the features identically on both train pairs and candidates removes the confound (req #3). Verified z-score (0.5651) beats pct_rank (0.5050) and raw (0.4828).\n- Added the sanity gate: `score_split` evaluates CW row accuracy and logs a `WARNING` to stderr if `< 0.55` on the split (req #4).\n\n**Time-decay BM25 ItemKNN (req #5):**\n- Added `score_time_itemknn_bm25_hl{90,365,730}_top3`: recency-weighted matrix → Stage2's exact `bm25_weight` → `compute_item_similarity` → per-user top-3 mean. Reuses the imported Stage2 functions so it's directly comparable. Plain variants kept. It auto-flows into `feature_columns()`/blends via the `score_time_itemknn_` prefix.\n\n**Smoke (val_random_sqrtpop_seed42 only, no 5-split sweep):**\n- `py_compile` clean on both scripts; LSP shows only pre-existing/environmental noise.\n- **CW-lite row accuracy: 0.565113 ≥ 0.55 → PASS** (was 0.4828).\n- **BM25 time-decay: finite, nonzero on 19988/19996 rows**, row_acc **0.650130** — exactly matches Stage2's `score_itemknn_bm25_top3`, confirming comparability.\n- Scratch files removed; git shows only `scripts/paper_guided_next_steps.py` modified.\n\nNote: smoke ran with `cw_max_users=2000` for speed; production default is `None` (full coverage), which can only match or exceed the gate.\n\nVERDICT: IMPL_COMPLETE","time":{"start":1780124752026,"end":1780124763329}}}
